isInPrimaryPartition

public boolean isInPrimaryPartition(boolean verbose)
Determines whether the local manager is in a primary partition, based on validated membership information passed in when this class is instantiated. A manager is considered to be in a primary partition if it has a simple majority of a) all potential members b) at least two out of three members.

Parameters:
verbose - prints information about how the determination is being made.
Returns:
true if the information indicates we are in a primary partition
